            def pretty_event_datetime

              def add_replace_menu_template menu_template_id, participation
        
      534. 
      
        
    534. 
          
          
          
        
      535. 
      
        
    535. 
          
          
                # Fetch new menu template
        
      536. 
      
        
    536. 
          
          
                new_menu_template = MenuTemplate.find(menu_template_id)
        
      537. 
      
        
    537. 
          
          
          
        
      538. 
      
        
    538. 
          
          
                # Fetch current event_vendor
        
      539. 
      
        
    539. 
          
          
                ev = fetch_event_vendor_by_vendor_id(new_menu_template.vendor_id)
        
      540. 
      
        
    540. 
          
          
          
        
      541. 
      
        
    541. 
          
          
                if !ev.nil? && ev.menu_template_id == new_menu_template.id
        
      542. 
      
        
    542. 
          
          
                  # Existing vendor, no new menu template.  Just update attributes.
        
      543. 
      
        
    543. 
          
          
                  ev.update_attributes!(:participation => participation)
        
      544. 
      
        
    544. 
          
          
                else
        
      545. 
      
        
    545. 
          
          
                  if !ev.nil?
        
      546. 
      
        
    546. 
          
          
                    # Existing vendor, new menu template.  Clean out line items, and update attributes from new template.
        
      547. 
      
        
    547. 
          
          
                    remove_all_menu_type_line_items(new_menu_template.vendor.id)
        
      548. 
      
        
    548. 
          
          
                    ev.update_attributes!(:menu_template => new_menu_template, :participation => participation,
        
      549. 
      
        
    549. 
          
          
                      :default_menu_cogs => new_menu_template.cogs, :default_menu_retail_price => new_menu_template.retail_price,
        
      550. 
      
        
    550. 
          
          
                      :default_menu_sell_price => calculate_sell_price_using_account_pricing_tier(new_menu_template.cogs),
        
      551. 
      
        
    551. 
          
          
                      :pricing_type => new_menu_template.pricing_type)
        
      552. 
      
        
    552. 
          
          
                  else
        
      553. 
      
        
    553. 
          
          
                    # New vendor.  Create a new container object.
        
      554. 
      
        
    554. 
          
          
                    ev = event_vendors.create!(
        
      555. 
      
        
    555. 
          
          
                      :vendor => Vendor.find(new_menu_template.vendor.id), :menu_template => new_menu_template, :participation => participation,
        
      556.

                      :default_menu_cogs => new_menu_template.cogs, :default_menu_retail_price => new_menu_template.retail_price,
        
      557.

                      :default_menu_sell_price => calculate_sell_price_using_account_pricing_tier(new_menu_template.cogs),
        
      558. 
      
        
    558. 
          
          
                      :pricing_type => new_menu_template.pricing_type)
        
      559. 
      
        
    559. 
          
          
                  end
        
      560. 
      
        
    560. 
          
          
          
        
      561. 
      
        
    561. 
          
          
                    # Fill in the new container object for this vendor
        
      562. 
      
        
    562. 
          
          
                    process_event_vendor(ev)
        
      563. 
      
        
    563. 
          
          
                    self.save
        
      564. 
      
        
    564. 
          
          
                end
        
      565.

              def calculate_sell_price_using_account_pricing_tier cogs
        
      642. 
      
        
    642. 
          
          
                if cogs.nil?
        
      643. 
      
        
    643. 
          
          
                  nil
        
      644. 
      
        
    644. 
          
          
                else
        
      645. 
      
        
    645.

      646. 
      
        
    646. 
          
          
          
        
      647. 
      
        
    647. 
          
          
                  if account_pricing_tier.nil?
        
      648. 
      
        
    648. 
          
          
                    # Assume GP of 25% if no pricing tier exists
        
      649. 
      
        
    649. 
          
          
                    sell_price = cogs / (1 - 25.0 / 100)
        
      650. 
      
        
    650. 
          
          
                  else
        
      651. 
      
        
    651. 
          
          
                    pricing_tier = PricingTier.find(account_pricing_tier.pricing_tier_id)
        
      652. 
      
        
    652. 
          
          
                    sell_price = cogs / (1 - pricing_tier.gross_profit / 100)
        
      653. 
      
        
    653. 
          
          
                  end
        
      654. 
      
        
    654. 
          
          
                  sell_price
        
      655. 
      
        
    655. 
          
          
                end
        
      656. 
      
        
    656. 
          
          
              end

              def destroy_line_items line_items_to_destroy, allow_recursion=true
        
      722. 
      
        
    722. 
          
          
                # Remove the opposing line item ID
        
      723. 
      
        
    723.

                # Remove the add on parent ID

                  destroy_line_items(add_ons, false) if add_ons.count > 0

            def event_time

    60. 
          
          
              return_val = event_start_time.strftime("%l:%M %p")
        
      61. 
      
        
    61. 
          
          
              return_val = return_val + " -" + event_end_time.strftime("%l:%M %p") unless event_end_time.nil?
        
      62. 
      
        
    62. 
          
          
              return_val
        
      63. 
      
        
    63. 
          
          
            end

            def vendor_selected

              self.vendor != nil

    67. 
          
          
            end

            def setup_time

              return_val = ""

    71. 
          
          
              if(setup_start_time)
        
      72.

                return_val = setup_start_time.strftime("%l:%M %p")

                return_val = return_val + "-" + setup_end_time.strftime("%l:%M %p") unless setup_end_time.nil?
        
      74.

              end

            end

            def schedule_friendly_string
        
      79. 
      
        
    79. 
          
          
              if self.schedule
        
      80. 
      
        
    80. 
          
          
                s = RecurringSelect.dirty_hash_to_rule(self.schedule)
        
      81. 
      
        
    81. 
          
          
                s.to_s
        
      82. 
      
        
    82. 
          
          
              end
        
      83. 
      
        
    83. 
          
          
            end
        
      84. 
      
        
    84. 
          
          
          
        
      85. 
      
        
    85. 
          1
          
            def active_friendly_string
        
      86. 
      
        
    86. 
          
          
              date = Date.today
        
      87. 
      
        
    87. 
          
          
              if self.pause_start_date && self.pause_end_date && (self.pause_start_date.to_date <= date && date < self.pause_end_date.to_date)
        
      88. 
      
        
    88. 
          
          
                "Paused until " + self.pause_end_date.strftime("%d %B %Y")
        
      89. 
      
        
    89. 
          
          
              elsif self.schedule_end_date && date > self.schedule_end_date.to_date
        
      90. 
      
        
    90. 
          
          
                "Expired"
        
      91. 
      
        
    91. 
          
          
              elsif date < self.schedule_start_date.to_date
        
      92. 
      
        
    92. 
          
          
                "Not starting until " + self.schedule_start_date.strftime("%d %B %Y")
        
      93. 
      
        
    93. 
          
          
              else
        
      94. 
      
        
    94. 
          
          
                "Active"
        
      95. 
      
        
    95. 
          
          
              end
        
      96. 
      
        
    96. 
          
          
            end

            # END UI display helper methods

          1
          
            def non_financial_product?
        
      102. 
      
        
    102. 
          
          
              Product.non_financial_values.include?(self.product)
        
      103. 
      
        
    103. 
          
          
            end
        
      104. 
      
        
    104. 
          
          
            
        
      105. 
      
        
    105. 
          1
          
            def process
        
      106. 
      
        
    106. 
          
          
          
        
      107. 
      
        
    107. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn "Starting event schedule processing for event schedule #{self.id}"
        
      108. 
      
        
    108. 
          
          
              rule = RecurringSelect.dirty_hash_to_rule(self.schedule)
        
      109. 
      
        
    109. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn  'Fetched rule: ' + rule.to_s + " for account: " + self.account.name
        
      110. 
      
        
    110. 
          
          
          
        
      111. 
      
        
    111. 
          
          
              # Determine the date to start processing.  This date actually holds a time,
        
      112. 
      
        
    112. 
          
          
              # but we'll be chopping the time component off
        
      113. 
      
        
    113. 
          
          
              date_to_start_processing = get_date_to_start_processing_at
        
      114. 
      
        
    114. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn  'Processing from: ' + date_to_start_processing.to_s
        
      115. 
      
        
    115. 
          
          
          
        
      116. 
      
        
    116. 
          
          
              # If there is a pause, then display it
        
      117. 
      
        
    117. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn  'With a pause from: ' + self.pause_start_date.to_s + ' until ' + self.pause_end_date.to_s if (self.pause_start_date && self.pause_end_date)
        
      118. 
      
        
    118. 
          
          
          
        
      119. 
      
        
    119. 
          
          
              # Create the schedule.  The schedule only has date-based rules right now,
        
      120. 
      
        
    120. 
          
          
              # so the time componets are apparently ignored.
        
      121. 
      
        
    121. 
          
          
              schedule = Schedule.new(date_to_start_processing) do |s|
        
      122. 
      
        
    122. 
          
          
                s.add_recurrence_rule(rule)
        
      123. 
      
        
    123. 
          
          
              end
        
      124. 
      
        
    124. 
          
          
          
        
      125. 
      
        
    125. 
          
          
              # Determine the date to stop
        
      126. 
      
        
    126. 
          
          
              date_to_stop = Time.now + self.days_to_schedule.days
        
      127. 
      
        
    127. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn  'Processing to: ' + date_to_stop.to_s
        
      128. 
      
        
    128. 
          
          
          
        
      129. 
      
        
    129. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn  'Schedule start date: ' + self.schedule_start_date.to_s unless self.schedule_start_date.nil?
        
      130. 
      
        
    130. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn  'Schedule final date: ' + self.schedule_end_date.to_s unless self.schedule_end_date.nil?
        
      131. 
      
        
    131. 
          
          
          
        
      132. 
      
        
    132. 
          
          
              # Determine the number of events to be created
        
      133. 
      
        
    133. 
          
          
              occurrences = schedule.occurrences(date_to_stop)
        
      134. 
      
        
    134. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn  'Events to be created: ' + occurrences.count.to_s
        
      135. 
      
        
    135. 
          
          
              
        
      136. 
      
        
    136. 
          
          
              cancel_dates = []
        
      137. 
      
        
    137. 
          
          
              (date_to_start_processing.to_date..date_to_stop.to_date).each { |date| cancel_dates.push(date)}
        
      138. 
      
        
    138. 
          
          
          
        
      139. 
      
        
    139. 
          
          
              # Loop the occurrences, and create/modify/cancel the events.
        
      140. 
      
        
    140. 
          
          
              occurrences.each { |day_to_schedule|
        
      141. 
      
        
    141. 
          
          
          
        
      142. 
      
        
    142. 
          
          
                cancel_dates -= [day_to_schedule.to_date]
        
      143. 
      
        
    143. 
          
          
          
        
      144. 
      
        
    144. 
          
          
                event_on_this_date = event_on_date(day_to_schedule.to_date)
        
      145. 
      
        
    145. 
          
          
          
        
      146. 
      
        
    146. 
          
          
                if is_schedule_active_on_date(day_to_schedule.to_date)
        
      147. 
      
        
    147. 
          
          
                  if !event_on_this_date || (event_on_this_date.status == Status::Event.canceled && event_on_this_date.cancellation_reason == CancellationReason.change_to_recurring_schedule)
        
      148. 
      
        
    148. 
          
          
                    # There is no event on this day, so create it
        
      149. 
      
        
    149. 
          
          
                    Rails.logger.warn   'Creating event for : ' + day_to_schedule.to_s
        
      150. 
      
        
    150. 
          
          
                    create_event day_to_schedule
        
      151. 
      
        
    151. 
          
          
                  elsif [Status::Event.auto_generated].include?(event_on_this_date.status)
        
      152. 
      
        
    152. 
          
          
                    # There is an event on this day, so modify if necessary
        
      153. 
      
        
    153. 
          
          
                    Rails.logger.warn   'Modifying event for : ' + day_to_schedule.to_s
        
      154. 
      
        
    154. 
          
          
                    modify_event event_on_this_date
        
      155. 
      
        
    155. 
          
          
                  end
        
      156. 
      
        
    156. 
          
          
                else
        
      157. 
      
        
    157. 
          
          
                  Rails.logger.warn   'Skipping: ' + day_to_schedule.to_s + ' schedule inactive (paused/stopped)'
        
      158. 
      
        
    158. 
          
          
                end
        
      159. 
      
        
    159. 
          
          
              }
        
      160. 
      
        
    160. 
          
          
          
        
      161. 
      
        
    161. 
          
          
              cancel_dates.each { |cancel_date|
        
      162. 
      
        
    162. 
          
          
          
        
      163. 
      
        
    163. 
          
          
                event_on_this_date = event_on_date(cancel_date)
        
      164. 
      
        
    164. 
          
          
          
        
      165. 
      
        
    165. 
          
          
                if event_on_this_date && [Status::Event.auto_generated].include?(event_on_this_date.status)
        
      166. 
      
        
    166. 
          
          
                  # No event should be on this day, so cancel it
        
      167. 
      
        
    167. 
          
          
                  Rails.logger.warn   'Canceling event for : ' + cancel_date.to_s
        
      168. 
      
        
    168. 
          
          
                  cancel_event event_on_this_date
        
      169. 
      
        
    169. 
          
          
                end
        
      170. 
      
        
    170. 
          
          
              }
        
      171. 
      
        
    171. 
          
          
          
        
      172. 
      
        
    172. 
          
          
              self.processed_until = date_to_stop
        
      173. 
      
        
    173. 
          
          
              self.save
        
      174. 
      
        
    174. 
          
          
            end
        
      175. 
      
        
    175. 
          
          
          
        
      176. 
      
        
    176. 
          1
          
            def is_schedule_active_on_date(date)
        
      177. 
      
        
    177. 
          
          
              schedule_active = true
        
      178. 
      
        
    178. 
          
          
              schedule_active &&= (self.pause_start_date.to_date > date || date >= self.pause_end_date.to_date) if (self.pause_start_date && self.pause_end_date)
        
      179. 
      
        
    179. 
          
          
              schedule_active &&= (date <= self.schedule_end_date.to_date) if (self.schedule_end_date)
        
      180. 
      
        
    180. 
          
          
              schedule_active
        
      181. 
      
        
    181. 
          
          
            end
        
      182. 
      
        
    182. 
          
          
          
        
      183. 
      
        
    183. 
          1
          
            def event_on_date(date)
        
      184. 
      
        
    184. 
          
          
              e = Event.select{|e| e.event_schedule_id == self.id && e.event_start_time.year == date.year && e.event_start_time.month == date.month && e.event_start_time.day == date.day }
        
      185. 
      
        
    185. 
          
          
              e.count > 0 ? e.first : nil
        
      186. 
      
        
    186. 
          
          
            end
        
      187. 
      
        
    187. 
          
          
          
        
      188. 
      
        
    188. 
          1
          
            def get_date_to_start_processing_at
        
      189. 
      
        
    189. 
          
          
              date_to_start_processing = Time.now + 1.days
        
      190. 
      
        
    190. 
          
          
              date_to_start_processing = self.schedule_start_date if date_to_start_processing < self.schedule_start_date
        
      191. 
      
        
    191. 
          
          
              date_to_start_processing
        
      192. 
      
        
    192. 
          
          
            end
        
      193. 
      
        
    193. 
          
          
          
        
      194. 
      
        
    194. 
          1
          
            def create_event(day_to_schedule)
        
      195. 
      
        
    195. 
          
          
              system_user = User.where(utility_account: true).first
        
      196. 
      
        
    196. 
          
          
              @event = Event.new(
        
      197. 
      
        
    197. 
          
          
                :name => "Recurring Event",
        
      198. 
      
        
    198. 
          
          
                :account_id => self.account_id,
        
      199. 
      
        
    199. 
          
          
                :product => self.product,
        
      200. 
      
        
    200. 
          
          
                :status => Status::Event.auto_generated,
        
      201. 
      
        
    201. 
          
          
                :contact_id => self.contact_id,
        
      202. 
      
        
    202. 
          
          
                :meal_period => self.meal_period,
        
      203. 
      
        
    203. 
          
          
                :location_id => self.location_id,
        
      204. 
      
        
    204. 
          
          
                :event_start_time => change_date_on_date_time_object(self.event_start_time, day_to_schedule),
        
      205. 
      
        
    205. 
          
          
                :event_end_time => change_date_on_date_time_object(self.event_end_time, day_to_schedule),
        
      206. 
      
        
    206. 
          
          
                :setup_start_time => change_date_on_date_time_object(self.setup_start_time, day_to_schedule),
        
      207. 
      
        
    207. 
          
          
                :setup_end_time => change_date_on_date_time_object(self.setup_end_time, day_to_schedule),
        
      208. 
      
        
    208. 
          
          
                :created_by => system_user,
        
      209. 
      
        
    209. 
          
          
                :quantity => self.quantity,
        
      210. 
      
        
    210. 
          
          
                :event_schedule_id => self.id,
        
      211. 
      
        
    211. 
          
          
                :event_owner_id => self.event_schedule_owner_id
        
      212. 
      
        
    212. 
          
          
              )
        
      213. 
      
        
    213. 
          
          
              
        
      214. 
      
        
    214. 
          
          
              Event.transaction do
        
      215. 
      
        
    215. 
          
          
                @event.save
        
      216. 
      
        
    216. 
          
          
                @event.update_transaction_method
        
      217. 
      
        
    217. 
          
          
                if(self.menu_template)
        
      218. 
      
        
    218. 
          
          
                  @event.add_replace_menu_template self.menu_template.id, self.quantity
        
      219. 
      
        
    219. 
          
          
                end
        
      220. 
      
        
    220. 
          
          
              end
        
      221. 
      
        
    221. 
          
          
              
        
      222. 
      
        
    222. 
          
          
              self.processed_until = day_to_schedule
        
      223. 
      
        
    223. 
          
          
              self.save
        
      224. 
      
        
    224. 
          
          
          
        
      225. 
      
        
    225. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn 'Created event with event_start_time: ' + @event.event_start_time.to_s
        
      226. 
      
        
    226. 
          
          
            end
        
      227. 
      
        
    227. 
          
          
          
        
      228. 
      
        
    228. 
          1
          
            def modify_event event
        
      229. 
      
        
    229. 
          
          
              event.update_attributes!(
        
      230. 
      
        
    230. 
          
          
                :account_id => self.account_id,
        
      231. 
      
        
    231. 
          
          
                :product => self.product,
        
      232. 
      
        
    232. 
          
          
                :status => Status::Event.auto_generated,
        
      233. 
      
        
    233. 
          
          
                :contact_id => self.contact_id,
        
      234. 
      
        
    234. 
          
          
                :meal_period => self.meal_period,
        
      235. 
      
        
    235. 
          
          
                :location_id => self.location_id,
        
      236. 
      
        
    236. 
          
          
                :event_start_time => event.event_start_time.nil? ? nil : change_date_on_date_time_object(self.event_start_time, event.event_start_time),
        
      237. 
      
        
    237. 
          
          
                :event_end_time => event.event_end_time.nil? ? nil : change_date_on_date_time_object(self.event_end_time, event.event_end_time),
        
      238. 
      
        
    238. 
          
          
                :setup_start_time => event.setup_start_time.nil? ? nil : change_date_on_date_time_object(self.setup_start_time, event.setup_start_time),
        
      239. 
      
        
    239. 
          
          
                :setup_end_time => event.setup_end_time.nil? ? nil : change_date_on_date_time_object(self.setup_end_time, event.setup_end_time),
        
      240. 
      
        
    240. 
          
          
                :quantity => self.quantity
        
      241. 
      
        
    241. 
          
          
              )
        
      242. 
      
        
    242. 
          
          
              
        
      243. 
      
        
    243. 
          
          
              if self.menu_template
        
      244. 
      
        
    244. 
          
          
                if event.event_vendors && event.event_vendors.count > 0
        
      245. 
      
        
    245. 
          
          
                  if (event.event_vendors.count == 1) && (event.event_vendors.first.vendor_id == self.menu_template.vendor_id) && (event.event_vendors.first.menu_template_id != self.menu_template.id)
        
      246. 
      
        
    246. 
          
          
                    # One vendor configured, same vendor, different menu template
        
      247. 
      
        
    247. 
          
          
                    event.add_replace_menu_template(self.menu_template.id, self.quantity)
        
      248. 
      
        
    248. 
          
          
                  elsif (event.event_vendors.count == 1) && (event.event_vendors.first.vendor_id != self.menu_template.vendor_id)
        
      249. 
      
        
    249. 
          
          
                    # One vendor configured, different vendor
        
      250. 
      
        
    250. 
          
          
                    event.remove_info_for_vendor(event.event_vendors.first.vendor_id)
        
      251. 
      
        
    251. 
          
          
                    event.add_replace_menu_template(self.menu_template.id, self.quantity)
        
      252. 
      
        
    252. 
          
          
                  elsif (event.event_vendors.count > 1)
        
      253. 
      
        
    253. 
          
          
                    # Multiple vendors.  Clear them all out, and add the new menu template.
        
      254. 
      
        
    254. 
          
          
                    vendor_ids = event.event_vendors.map{|ev| ev.vendor_id}
        
      255. 
      
        
    255. 
          
          
                    vendor_ids.each {|id| event.remove_info_for_vendor(id)}
        
      256. 
      
        
    256. 
          
          
                    event.add_replace_menu_template(self.menu_template.id, self.quantity)
        
      257. 
      
        
    257. 
          
          
                  end
        
      258. 
      
        
    258. 
          
          
                else
        
      259. 
      
        
    259. 
          
          
                  # No event vendors, so add one
        
      260. 
      
        
    260. 
          
          
                  event.add_replace_menu_template(self.menu_template.id, self.quantity)
        
      261. 
      
        
    261. 
          
          
                end
        
      262. 
      
        
    262. 
          
          
              else
        
      263. 
      
        
    263. 
          
          
                # No menu template configured.  Clear out all the existing vendors.
        
      264. 
      
        
    264. 
          
          
                if event.event_vendors
        
      265. 
      
        
    265. 
          
          
                  vendor_ids = event.event_vendors.map{|ev| ev.vendor_id}
        
      266. 
      
        
    266. 
          
          
                  vendor_ids.each {|id| event.remove_info_for_vendor(id)}
        
      267. 
      
        
    267. 
          
          
                end
        
      268. 
      
        
    268. 
          
          
              end
        
      269. 
      
        
    269. 
          
          
          
        
      270. 
      
        
    270. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn 'Modified event with event_start_time: ' + event.event_start_time.to_s
        
      271. 
      
        
    271. 
          
          
            end
        
      272. 
      
        
    272. 
          
          
          
        
      273. 
      
        
    273. 
          1
          
            def cancel_event(event)
        
      274. 
      
        
    274. 
          
          
              event.status = Status::Event.canceled
        
      275. 
      
        
    275. 
          
          
              event.cancellation_reason = CancellationReason.change_to_recurring_schedule
        
      276. 
      
        
    276. 
          
          
              event.save
        
      277. 
      
        
    277. 
          
          
              Rails.logger.warn 'Cancelled event with event_start_time: ' + event.event_start_time.to_s
        
      278. 
      
        
    278. 
          
          
            end
        
      279. 
      
        
    279. 
          
          
          
        
      280. 
      
        
    280. 
          1
          
            def change_date_on_date_time_object(date_from, date_to)
        
      281. 
      
        
    281. 
          
          
              if date_from
        
      282. 
      
        
    282. 
          
          
                date_from = date_from.change(day: date_to.day)
        
      283. 
      
        
    283. 
          
          
                date_from = date_from.change(month: date_to.month)
        
      284. 
      
        
    284. 
          
          
                date_from = date_from.change(year: date_to.year)
        
      285. 
      
        
    285. 
          
          
              end
        
      286. 
      
        
    286.

          1
          
              def process_add_ons inventory_item_to_quantity
        
      210. 
      
        
    210. 
          
          
          
        
      211. 
      
        
    211. 
          
          
                # If no opposing line item, try to set one.
        
      212. 
      
        
    212. 
          
          
                if self.opposing_line_item.nil?
        
      213. 
      
        
    213. 
          
          
                  possible_opposing_line_items = self.event.line_items.select{|li| !li.billable_party.nil? && (li.inventory_item_id == self.inventory_item_id)}
        
      214. 
      
        
    214. 
          
          
                  if possible_opposing_line_items.count > 0
        
      215. 
      
        
    215. 
          
          
                    self.opposing_line_item_id = possible_opposing_line_items.first.id
        
      216. 
      
        
    216. 
          
          
                    self.save
        
      217. 
      
        
    217. 
          
          
                  end
        
      218. 
      
        
    218. 
          
          
                end
        
      219. 
      
        
    219. 
          
          
          
        
      220. 
      
        
    220. 
          
          
                items_to_delete = self.add_ons.select{|li| !li.inventory_item_id.nil?}
        
      221. 
      
        
    221. 
          
          
                if items_to_delete.count > 0
        
      222. 
      
        
    222. 
          
          
                  self.event.destroy_line_items(items_to_delete)
        
      223. 
      
        
    223. 
          
          
                  self.add_ons.delete(items_to_delete)
        
      224. 
      
        
    224. 
          
          
                end
        
      225. 
      
        
    225. 
          
          
          
        
      226. 
      
        
    226. 
          
          
                if !self.opposing_line_item.nil?
        
      227. 
      
        
    227. 
          
          
                  opposing_items_to_delete = self.opposing_line_item.add_ons.select{|li| !li.inventory_item_id.nil?}
        
      228. 
      
        
    228. 
          
          
                  if opposing_items_to_delete.count > 0
        
      229. 
      
        
    229. 
          
          
                    self.opposing_line_item.event.destroy_line_items(opposing_items_to_delete)
        
      230. 
      
        
    230. 
          
          
                    self.opposing_line_item.add_ons.delete(opposing_items_to_delete)
        
      231. 
      
        
    231. 
          
          
                  end
        
      232. 
      
        
    232. 
          
          
                end
        
      233. 
      
        
    233. 
          
          
          
        
      234. 
      
        
    234. 
          
          
                inventory_item_to_quantity.each do |inventory_item_id_string, quantity_string|
        
      235. 
      
        
    235. 
          
          
          
        
      236. 
      
        
    236. 
          
          
                  # Convert inputs variables to ints
        
      237. 
      
        
    237. 
          
          
                  inventory_item_id = inventory_item_id_string.to_i
        
      238. 
      
        
    238. 
          
          
                  quantity = quantity_string.to_i
        
      239. 
      
        
    239. 
          
          
          
        
      240. 
      
        
    240. 
          
          
                  if quantity > 0
        
      241. 
      
        
    241. 
          
          
                    # We want this add-on
        
      242. 
      
        
    242. 
          
          
                    new_line_items = self.event.create_line_item_from_inventory_item_id(inventory_item_id, quantity, true, true, "")
        
      243. 
      
        
    243. 
          
          
                    self.add_ons.push(new_line_items[0])
        
      244. 
      
        
    244. 
          
          
                    self.opposing_line_item.add_ons.push(new_line_items[1]) if !self.opposing_line_item.nil?
        
      245. 
      
        
    245. 
          
          
                  end
        
      246. 
      
        
    246. 
          
          
                end
        
      247. 
      
        
    247. 
          
          
          
        
      248. 
      
        
    248. 
          
          
                # We have all the line items now.  Loop the groups.
        
      249. 
      
        
    249. 
          
          
                inventory_item.option_groups.each do |og|
        
      250. 
      
        
    250. 
          
          
          
        
      251. 
      
        
    251. 
          
          
                  # Sort the inventory items in the group by price
        
      252. 
      
        
    252. 
          
          
                  sorted_inventory_item_ids = og.inventory_items.sort_by{|i| i.cogs_cents - i.premium_price_cents}.map{|i| i.id}.flatten
        
      253. 
      
        
    253. 
          
          
          
        
      254. 
      
        
    254. 
          
          
                  # Determine which line items are in this group
        
      255. 
      
        
    255. 
          
          
                  group_line_items = self.add_ons.select{|li| sorted_inventory_item_ids.include?(li.inventory_item_id)}
        
      256. 
      
        
    256. 
          
          
          
        
      257. 
      
        
    257. 
          
          
                  # Sort the line items
        
      258. 
      
        
    258. 
          
          
                  group_line_items = group_line_items.sort_by{|li| sorted_inventory_item_ids.index(li.inventory_item_id)}
        
      259. 
      
        
    259. 
          
          
          
        
      260. 
      
        
    260. 
          
          
                  included_count = 0
        
      261. 
      
        
    261. 
          
          
                  index = 0
        
      262. 
      
        
    262. 
          
          
                  while included_count < [og.included, group_line_items.count].min do
        
      263. 
      
        
    263. 
          
          
          
        
      264. 
      
        
    264. 
          
          
                    included_count += group_line_items[index].quantity
        
      265. 
      
        
    265. 
          
          
                    if included_count > og.included
        
      266. 
      
        
    266. 
          
          
          
        
      267. 
      
        
    267. 
          
          
                      # Create a new line item for the "full price" remainder
        
      268. 
      
        
    268. 
          
          
                      new_line_items = self.event.create_line_item_from_inventory_item_id(group_line_items[index].inventory_item.id, included_count - og.included, true, true, "")
        
      269. 
      
        
    269. 
          
          
                      self.add_ons.push(new_line_items[0])
        
      270. 
      
        
    270. 
          
          
                      self.opposing_line_item.add_ons.push(new_line_items[1])
        
      271. 
      
        
    271. 
          
          
          
        
      272. 
      
        
    272. 
          
          
                      # Alter the line item for the "included" price, and reduce the quantity
        
      273. 
      
        
    273. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].unit_price_expense = InventoryItem.find(group_line_items[index].inventory_item).premium_price
        
      274. 
      
        
    274. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].quantity -= (included_count - og.included)
        
      275. 
      
        
    275. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].name += " (included)"
        
      276. 
      
        
    276. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].save
        
      277. 
      
        
    277. 
          
          
          
        
      278. 
      
        
    278. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].opposing_line_item.unit_price_revenue = self.event.calculate_sell_price_using_account_pricing_tier(group_line_items[index].unit_price_expense)
        
      279. 
      
        
    279. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].opposing_line_item.quantity -= (included_count - og.included)
        
      280. 
      
        
    280. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].opposing_line_item.name += " (included)"
        
      281. 
      
        
    281. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].opposing_line_item.save
        
      282. 
      
        
    282. 
          
          
                    else
        
      283. 
      
        
    283. 
          
          
                      # Alter the line item for the "included" price
        
      284. 
      
        
    284. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].unit_price_expense = InventoryItem.find(group_line_items[index].inventory_item).premium_price
        
      285. 
      
        
    285. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].name += " (included)"
        
      286. 
      
        
    286. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].save
        
      287. 
      
        
    287. 
          
          
          
        
      288. 
      
        
    288. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].opposing_line_item.unit_price_revenue = self.event.calculate_sell_price_using_account_pricing_tier(group_line_items[index].unit_price_expense)
        
      289. 
      
        
    289. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].opposing_line_item.name += " (included)"
        
      290. 
      
        
    290. 
          
          
                      group_line_items[index].opposing_line_item.save
        
      291. 
      
        
    291. 
          
          
                    end
        
      292. 
      
        
    292. 
          
          
          
        
      293. 
      
        
    293. 
          
          
                    index += 1
        
      294. 
      
        
    294. 
          
          
                  end
        
      295. 
      
        
    295. 
          
          
          
        
      296. 
      
        
    296. 
          
          
                end
        
      297. 
      
        
    297. 
          
          
              end
        
      298. 
      
        
    298. 
          
          
          
        
      299. 
      
        
    299. 
          1
          
              def required_options_satisfied
        
      300. 
      
        
    300. 
          
          
                if self.inventory_item_id.nil?
        
      301. 
      
        
    301. 
          
          
                  true
        
      302. 
      
        
    302. 
          
          
                else
        
      303. 
      
        
    303. 
          
          
                  satisfied = true
        
      304. 
      
        
    304. 
          
          
                  self.inventory_item.option_groups.each do |og|
        
      305. 
      
        
    305. 
          
          
                    inventory_item_ids = og.inventory_items.map{|i| i.id}.flatten
        
      306. 
      
        
    306. 
          
          
                    group_qty_sum = self.add_ons.select{|li| inventory_item_ids.include?(li.inventory_item_id)}.inject(0) { |sum, li| sum + li.quantity }
        
      307. 
      
        
    307. 
          
          
                    if group_qty_sum < og.required
        
      308. 
      
        
    308. 
          
          
                      satisfied = false
        
      309. 
      
        
    309. 
          
          
                    end
        
      310. 
      
        
    310. 
          
          
                  end
        
      311. 
      
        
    311. 
          
          
                  satisfied
        
      312. 
      
        
    312.

      91. 
      
        
    91. 
          
          
            #
        
      92. 
      
        
    92. 
          
          
            # Optional params: {
        
      93. 
      
        
    93. 
          
          
            #   :select_order_transaction_id => original transaction id (of pay-in)
        
      94. 
      
        
    94. 
          
          
            #   :account_id => account id
        
      95. 
      
        
    95. 
          
          
            #   :notes => notes to store in the select order transaction table
        
      96. 
      
        
    96. 
          
          
            #   :customer_id => braintree customer id (TODO: where do we get this?)
        
      97. 
      
        
    97. 
          
          
            # }
        
      98. 
      
        
    98. 
          
          
            #
        
      99. 
      
        
    99. 
          1
          
            def braintree_refund params
        
      100. 
      
        
    100. 
          
          
              messages = ''
        
      101. 
      
        
    101. 
          
          
              ret_val = true
        
      102. 
      
        
    102. 
          
          
          
        
      103. 
      
        
    103. 
          
          
              refund_amount = params[:amount].to_f
        
      104. 
      
        
    104. 
          
          
          
        
      105. 
      
        
    105. 
          
          
              if params[:select_order_transaction_id]
        
      106. 
      
        
    106. 
          
          
                # Transaction id has been passed in
        
      107. 
      
        
    107. 
          
          
                orig_transaction = Select::SelectOrderTransaction.find_by_id params[:select_order_transaction_id]
        
      108. 
      
        
    108. 
          
          
                return false if !orig_transaction or orig_transaction.is_refund
        
      109. 
      
        
    109. 
          
          
                # If the amounts are identical cancel the transaction itself
        
      110. 
      
        
    110. 
          
          
                # refund that transaction and return
        
      111. 
      
        
    111. 
          
          
                if refund_amount == orig_transaction.amount
        
      112. 
      
        
    112. 
          
          
                  return self.braintree_refund_transaction orig_transaction
        
      113. 
      
        
    113. 
          
          
                end
        
      114. 
      
        
    114. 
          
          
                # Otherwise fall thru, the transaction id supplied is ignored
        
      115. 
      
        
    115. 
          
          
                # only the amount is used.
        
      116. 
      
        
    116. 
          
          
              end
        
      117. 
      
        
    117. 
          
          
          
        
      118. 
      
        
    118. 
          
          
              # No transaction id, just amount available so this refund may involve
        
      119. 
      
        
    119. 
          
          
              # one or more transactions that need to be reversed
        
      120. 
      
        
    120. 
          
          
              self.select_order_transactions.payments.order('amount asc').each do |transaction|
        
      121. 
      
        
    121. 
          
          
                break if refund_amount <= 0.to_f
        
      122. 
      
        
    122. 
          
          
                if transaction.amount <= refund_amount
        
      123. 
      
        
    123. 
          
          
                  # Found a transaction that can be completely refunded (amt <= refund_amount)
        
      124. 
      
        
    124. 
          
          
                  ret_val = self.braintree_refund_transaction transaction
        
      125. 
      
        
    125. 
          
          
                  refund_amount = refund_amount - transaction.amount if ret_val
        
      126. 
      
        
    126. 
          
          
                elsif (transaction.amount > refund_amount) && (refund_amount > 0.to_f)
        
      127. 
      
        
    127. 
          
          
                  # Transaction amount > refund amount: special case processing
        
      128. 
      
        
    128. 
          
          
                  # Deduct refund amount from this transactions' amount
        
      129. 
      
        
    129. 
          
          
                  # and create a new transaction superceding this transaction
        
      130. 
      
        
    130. 
          
          
                  #
        
      131. 
      
        
    131. 
          
          
                  # This is used when creating the new transaction row
        
      132. 
      
        
    132. 
          
          
                  # Refund is FALSE assuming that the orig transaction is not settled/settling
        
      133. 
      
        
    133. 
          
          
                  # supercede is TRUE assuming that a new select_order_transaction is required
        
      134. 
      
        
    134. 
          
          
                  # to supercede a partial refund. It will be set to FALSE if the (running)
        
      135. 
      
        
    135. 
          
          
                  # refund amount exactly matches an available transaction amount.
        
      136. 
      
        
    136. 
          
          
                  transaction_refund = false
        
      137. 
      
        
    137. 
          
          
                  supercede_transaction = true
        
      138. 
      
        
    138. 
          
          
                  post_refund_amount = 0.to_f
        
      139. 
      
        
    139. 
          
          
                  new_transaction_amount = 0.to_f
        
      140. 
      
        
    140. 
          
          
          
        
      141. 
      
        
    141. 
          
          
                  if [:settled, :settling].include? transaction.status.to_sym
        
      142. 
      
        
    142. 
          
          
                    # If the original transaction being partially refunded has already been
        
      143. 
      
        
    143. 
          
          
                    # settled or is in the process of settling then we should refund the
        
      144. 
      
        
    144. 
          
          
                    # amount.
        
      145. 
      
        
    145. 
          
          
                    result = Braintree::Transaction.refund(transaction.transaction_id, refund_amount)
        
      146. 
      
        
    146. 
          
          
                    result_data = self.braintree_result_data result
        
      147. 
      
        
    147. 
          
          
                    transaction_refund = true
        
      148. 
      
        
    148. 
          
          
                    # New transaction amount will be the actual refund amount
        
      149. 
      
        
    149. 
          
          
                    # The existing transaction's amount will change to post_refund_amount
        
      150. 
      
        
    150. 
          
          
                    new_transaction_amount = refund_amount
        
      151. 
      
        
    151. 
          
          
                    post_refund_amount = transaction.amount - refund_amount
        
      152. 
      
        
    152. 
          
          
                    ret_val = result.success?
        
      153. 
      
        
    153. 
          
          
                  elsif [:authorized].include? transaction.status.to_sym
        
      154. 
      
        
    154. 
          
          
                    # If the original transaction is just authorized  do nothing at this point
        
      155. 
      
        
    155. 
          
          
                    # (we've authorized a higher dollar amount than what will be charged).
        
      156. 
      
        
    156. 
          
          
                    # Set the result_data based on the orig transaction about to be superceded.
        
      157. 
      
        
    157. 
          
          
                    result_data = {
        
      158. 
      
        
    158. 
          
          
                      transaction_id:   transaction.transaction_id,
        
      159. 
      
        
    159. 
          
          
                      transaction_type: transaction.transaction_type,
        
      160. 
      
        
    160. 
          
          
                      status:           transaction.status,
        
      161. 
      
        
    161. 
          
          
                      response:         transaction.response,
        
      162. 
      
        
    162. 
          
          
                      cc_last4:         transaction.cc_last4,
        
      163. 
      
        
    163. 
          
          
                      card_type:        transaction.card_type,
        
      164. 
      
        
    164. 
          
          
                      expiration_date:  transaction.expiration_date
        
      165. 
      
        
    165. 
          
          
                    }
        
      166. 
      
        
    166. 
          
          
                    ret_val = true
        
      167. 
      
        
    167. 
          
          
                    # New transaction amount will be the reduced total after subtracting
        
      168. 
      
        
    168. 
          
          
                    # refund amount
        
      169. 
      
        
    169. 
          
          
                    new_transaction_amount = transaction.amount - refund_amount
        
      170. 
      
        
    170. 
          
          
          
        
      171. 
      
        
    171. 
          
          
                    # If the new authorized amount (transaction.amount == refund amount) is zero
        
      172. 
      
        
    172. 
          
          
                    # then just void the current transaction. DO NOT create a superceded version
        
      173. 
      
        
    173. 
          
          
                    # if this transaction since its not needed.
        
      174. 
      
        
    174. 
          
          
                    if transaction.amount == refund_amount
        
      175. 
      
        
    175. 
          
          
                      result = Braintree::Transaction.void(transaction.transaction_id)
        
      176. 
      
        
    176. 
          
          
                      supercede_transaction = false
        
      177. 
      
        
    177. 
          
          
                    end
        
      178. 
      
        
    178. 
          
          
                  else
        
      179. 
      
        
    179. 
          
          
                    supercede_transaction = false
        
      180. 
      
        
    180. 
          
          
                    next # This is a "submitted_for_settlement" status, cannot use, continue
        
      181. 
      
        
    181. 
          
          
                  end
        
      182. 
      
        
    182. 
          
          
          
        
      183. 
      
        
    183. 
          
          
                  if result_data[:transaction_id] && supercede_transaction
        
      184. 
      
        
    184. 
          
          
                    # Create the select order transaction row only to record a non-zero amount
        
      185. 
      
        
    185. 
          
          
                    # The refund of a full transaction resulting in a zero left-over amount
        
      186. 
      
        
    186. 
          
          
                    # does not need an updated transaction row.
        
      187. 
      
        
    187. 
          
          
                    t = Select::SelectOrderTransaction.create(
        
      188. 
      
        
    188. 
          
          
                            # Snappea data
        
      189. 
      
        
    189. 
          
          
                            user_id:          user.id,
        
      190. 
      
        
    190. 
          
          
                            select_event_id:  self.select_event.id,
        
      191. 
      
        
    191. 
          
          
                            select_order_id:  self.id,
        
      192. 
      
        
    192. 
          
          
                            card_id:          (transaction_refund ? nil : transaction.card_id),
        
      193. 
      
        
    193. 
          
          
                            account_id:       (transaction_refund ? nil : transaction.account_id),
        
      194. 
      
        
    194. 
          
          
                            timestamp:        Time.now,
        
      195. 
      
        
    195. 
          
          
                            amount:           new_transaction_amount,
        
      196. 
      
        
    196. 
          
          
                            is_refund:        transaction_refund,
        
      197. 
      
        
    197. 
          
          
                            notes:            (transaction_refund ? params[:notes] : transaction.notes),
        
      198. 
      
        
    198. 
          
          
                            # Braintree data
        
      199. 
      
        
    199. 
          
          
                            superceded:       false,
        
      200. 
      
        
    200. 
          
          
                            customer_id:      nil,                      # TODO
        
      201. 
      
        
    201. 
          
          
                            transaction_id:   result_data[:transaction_id],
        
      202. 
      
        
    202. 
          
          
                            transaction_type: result_data[:transaction_type],
        
      203. 
      
        
    203. 
          
          
                            status:           result_data[:status],
        
      204. 
      
        
    204. 
          
          
                            response:         result_data[:response],
        
      205. 
      
        
    205. 
          
          
                            # Metadata
        
      206. 
      
        
    206. 
          
          
                            cc_last4:         result_data[:cc_last4],
        
      207. 
      
        
    207. 
          
          
                            card_type:        result_data[:card_type],
        
      208. 
      
        
    208. 
          
          
                            expiration_date:  result_data[:expiration_date]
        
      209. 
      
        
    209. 
          
          
                          )
        
      210. 
      
        
    210. 
          
          
          
        
      211. 
      
        
    211. 
          
          
                    transaction.notes ||= ''
        
      212. 
      
        
    212. 
          
          
          
        
      213. 
      
        
    213. 
          
          
                    if transaction_refund
        
      214. 
      
        
    214. 
          
          
                      # Update the existing transaction, set post refund amount
        
      215. 
      
        
    215. 
          
          
                      # if the amount is being adjusted AFTER settlement
        
      216. 
      
        
    216. 
          
          
                      transaction.update_attributes({
        
      217. 
      
        
    217. 
          
          
                        amount: post_refund_amount,  # For partial refunds
        
      218. 
      
        
    218. 
          
          
                        notes: transaction.notes + "\n" + sprintf("$%.02f", new_transaction_amount) + " refunded in transaction: " + t.id.to_s
        
      219. 
      
        
    219. 
          
          
                      })
        
      220. 
      
        
    220. 
          
          
                    else
        
      221. 
      
        
    221. 
          
          
                      # Update the existing transaction, set superceded to TRUE
        
      222. 
      
        
    222. 
          
          
                      # if the amount is being adjusted BEFORE settlement
        
      223. 
      
        
    223. 
          
          
                      transaction.update_attributes({
        
      224. 
      
        
    224. 
          
          
                        superceded: true,
        
      225. 
      
        
    225. 
          
          
                        notes:      transaction.notes + "\nSuperceded by transaction: " + t.id.to_s
        
      226. 
      
        
    226. 
          
          
                      })
        
      227. 
      
        
    227. 
          
          
                    end
        
      228. 
      
        
    228. 
          
          
          
        
      229. 
      
        
    229. 
          
          
                    refund_amount -= new_transaction_amount
        
      230. 
      
        
    230. 
          
          
                  end
        
      231. 
      
        
    231. 
          
          
                  # Complete amount has been refunded using this transaction
        
      232. 
      
        
    232. 
          
          
                  # So we can return back to caller
        
      233. 
      
        
    233. 
          
          
                  return [ret_val, messages]
        
      234. 
      
        
    234. 
          
          
                end
        
      235. 
      
        
    235. 
          
          
              end
        
      236. 
      
        
    236. 
          
          
          
        
      237. 
      
        
    237. 
          
          
              # If we still have a "leftover" refund amount, then our attempts to refund
        
      238. 
      
        
    238. 
          
          
              # the amount have failed. This is because some transactions have been
        
      239. 
      
        
    239. 
          
          
              # submitted for settlement and cannot be refunded/touched until the
        
      240. 
      
        
    240. 
          
          
              # braintree status changes to settled or settling.
        
      241. 
      
        
    241. 
          
          
              if refund_amount > 0.to_f
        
      242. 
      
        
    242. 
          
          
                messages += "Cannot refund transactions that are submitted for settlement but not yet settled.\n"
        
      243. 
      
        
    243. 
          
          
                ret_val = false
        
      244. 
      
        
    244. 
          
          
              end
        
      245. 
      
        
    245. 
          
          
          
        
      246. 
      
        
    246. 
          
          
              # Return the status back (true = all ok)
        
      247. 
      
        
    247. 
          
          
              [ret_val, messages]
        
      248. 
      
        
    248. 
          
          
            end
        
      249. 
      
        
    249. 
          
          
          
        
      250. 
      
        
    250. 
          
          
            # Refund an existing transaction & save it as a new select order transaction
        
      251. 
      
        
    251. 
          
          
            # --------------------------------------------------------------------------
        
      252. 
      
        
    252. 
          
          
            # transaction => the transaction to refund or void
        
      253. 
      
        
    253. 
          
          
            #
        
      254. 
      
        
    254. 
          1
          
            def braintree_refund_transaction transaction
        
      255. 
      
        
    255. 
          
          
              if transaction && !transaction.is_refund && !transaction.superceded
        
      256. 
      
        
    256. 
          
          
                # Attempt to refund the requested amount
        
      257. 
      
        
    257. 
          
          
                if [:settled, :settling].include? transaction.status.to_sym
        
      258. 
      
        
    258. 
          
          
                  result = Braintree::Transaction.refund(transaction.transaction_id)
        
      259. 
      
        
    259. 
          
          
                elsif [:authorized, :submitted_for_settlement].include? transaction.status.to_sym
        
      260. 
      
        
    260. 
          
          
                  result = Braintree::Transaction.void(transaction.transaction_id)
        
      261. 
      
        
    261. 
          
          
                else
        
      262. 
      
        
    262. 
          
          
                  # Cannot handle the current transaction state
        
      263. 
      
        
    263. 
          
          
                  return false
        
      264. 
      
        
    264. 
          
          
                end
        
      265. 
      
        
    265. 
          
          
          
        
      266. 
      
        
    266. 
          
          
                result_data = self.braintree_result_data result
        
      267. 
      
        
    267. 
          
          
          
        
      268. 
      
        
    268. 
          
          
                if result_data[:transaction_id]
        
      269. 
      
        
    269. 
          
          
                  transaction.notes ||= ''
        
      270. 
      
        
    270. 
          
          
                  # Create the select order transaction row
        
      271. 
      
        
    271. 
          
          
                  t = Select::SelectOrderTransaction.create(
        
      272. 
      
        
    272. 
          
          
                          # Snappea data
        
      273. 
      
        
    273. 
          
          
                          user_id:          user.id,
        
      274. 
      
        
    274. 
          
          
                          select_event_id:  self.select_event.id,
        
      275. 
      
        
    275. 
          
          
                          select_order_id:  self.id,
        
      276. 
      
        
    276. 
          
          
                          card_id:          nil,      # TODO
        
      277. 
      
        
    277. 
          
          
                          account_id:       nil,      # TODO
        
      278. 
      
        
    278. 
          
          
                          timestamp:        Time.now,
        
      279. 
      
        
    279. 
          
          
                          amount:           transaction.amount,
        
      280. 
      
        
    280. 
          
          
                          is_refund:        true,
        
      281. 
      
        
    281. 
          
          
                          notes:            transaction.notes,
        
      282. 
      
        
    282. 
          
          
                          # Braintree data
        
      283. 
      
        
    283. 
          
          
                          superceded:       false,
        
      284. 
      
        
    284. 
          
          
                          customer_id:      nil,      # TODO
        
      285. 
      
        
    285. 
          
          
                          transaction_id:   result_data[:transaction_id],
        
      286. 
      
        
    286. 
          
          
                          transaction_type: result_data[:transaction_type],
        
      287. 
      
        
    287. 
          
          
                          status:           result_data[:status],
        
      288. 
      
        
    288. 
          
          
                          response:         result_data[:response],
        
      289. 
      
        
    289. 
          
          
                          # Metadata
        
      290. 
      
        
    290. 
          
          
                          cc_last4:         result_data[:cc_last4],
        
      291. 
      
        
    291. 
          
          
                          card_type:        result_data[:card_type],
        
      292. 
      
        
    292. 
          
          
                          expiration_date:  result_data[:expiration_date]
        
      293. 
      
        
    293. 
          
          
                        )
        
      294. 
      
        
    294. 
          
          
          
        
      295. 
      
        
    295. 
          
          
                  # Update the existing transaction by superceding it
        
      296. 
      
        
    296. 
          
          
                  transaction.update_attributes({
        
      297. 
      
        
    297. 
          
          
                    superceded: true,
        
      298. 
      
        
    298. 
          
          
                    notes:      transaction.notes + "\nSuperceded by transaction: " + t.id.to_s
        
      299. 
      
        
    299. 
          
          
                  })
        
      300. 
      
        
    300. 
          
          
                end
        
      301. 
      
        
    301. 
          
          
          
        
      302. 
      
        
    302. 
          
          
                # Return true if successful
        
      303. 
      
        
    303. 
          
          
                result.success?
        
      304. 
      
        
    304. 
          
          
              else
        
      305. 
      
        
    305. 
          
          
                # No such transaction id
        
      306. 
      
        
    306. 
          
          
                false
        
      307. 
      
        
    307. 
          
          
              end
        
      308. 
      
        
    308. 
          
          
            end
        
      309. 
      
        
    309. 
          
          
          
        
      310. 
      
        
    310. 
          1
          
            def braintree_result_data result
        
      311. 
      
        
    311. 
          
          
              transaction = result.transaction
        
      312. 
      
        
    312. 
          
          
              status = nil
        
      313. 
      
        
    313. 
          
          
          
        
      314. 
      
        
    314. 
          
          
              if result.success?
        
      315. 
      
        
    315. 
          
          
                response = :success
        
      316. 
      
        
    316. 
          
          
                status = transaction.status
        
      317. 
      
        
    317. 
          
          
              else
        
      318. 
      
        
    318. 
          
          
                response = ''
        
      319. 
      
        
    319. 
          
          
                if transaction && transaction.processor_response_code
        
      320. 
      
        
    320. 
          
          
                  response = '(' + transaction.processor_response_code + ') ' + transaction.processor_response_text
        
      321. 
      
        
    321. 
          
          
                  status = transaction.status
        
      322. 
      
        
    322. 
          
          
                elsif transaction && transaction.gateway_rejection_reason
        
      323. 
      
        
    323. 
          
          
                  response = 'Gateway rejection: ' + transaction.gateway_rejection_reason
        
      324. 
      
        
    324. 
          
          
                  status = transaction.status
        
      325. 
      
        
    325. 
          
          
                end
        
      326. 
      
        
    326. 
          
          
              end
        
      327. 
      
        
    327. 
          
          
          
        
      328. 
      
        
    328. 
          
          
              { transaction_id:   (transaction ? transaction.id   : nil),
        
      329. 
      
        
    329. 
          
          
                transaction_type: (transaction ? transaction.type : nil),
        
      330. 
      
        
    330. 
          
          
                cc_last4:         (transaction ? transaction.credit_card_details.last_4 : 'XXXX'),
        
      331. 
      
        
    331. 
          
          
                card_type:        (transaction ? transaction.credit_card_details.card_type : '?'),
        
      332. 
      
        
    332. 
          
          
                expiration_date:  (transaction ? transaction.credit_card_details.expiration_date  : 'MM/YYYY'),
        
      333. 
      
        
    333. 
          
          
                status:           status,
        
      334. 
      
        
    334. 
          
          
                response:         response }
        
      335. 
      
        
    335. 
          
          
            end
        
      336. 
      
        
    336. 
          
          
          
        
      337. 
      
        
    337. 
          1
          
            def braintree_update_transaction_status(t)
        
      338. 
      
        
    338. 
          
          
              transaction = Braintree::Transaction.find(t.transaction_id)
        
      339. 
      
        
    339. 
          
          
              # Operate on it only if the transaction status has changed
        
      340. 
      
        
    340. 
          
          
              # since the last time
        
      341. 
      
        
    341. 
          
          
              if transaction.status != t.status
        
      342. 
      
        
    342. 
          
          
                notes = t.notes
        
      343. 
      
        
    343. 
          
          
                notes ||= ''
        
      344. 
      
        
    344. 
          
          
          
        
      345.

            def is_eligible_for_catering?
        
      351.
